Uche Nnadi, one of the notable faces on the popular sitcom, ‘The Johnsons,’ is mourning the loss of his aged dad, Nnandi Jacob Ndubuisi. Nnadi, who plays the role of Goodluck in the sitcom, announced the passing away of his dad on March 10. The Nation gathered that the late Nnadi passed away at the age of 63 on March 1. In his words, the actor and comedian said, “Your departure has broken and transformed me into a man not by gender but by the willingness to do what great men do knowing that death is the end of every mortal. I love you, dad, I will never forget you. Our hero, our warrior….” Nnadi has been a regular face on the sitcom, which continues to garner viewership and popularity across the Nigerian populace.